      <h1 class='title'>Transport-related Emissions</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 cc1715-6WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1715ws' title='Col. 1715WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1715WS' name='column_1715ws' href='#column_1715ws' rel='bookmark'>1715WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_380'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-adam-price' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_380' title='Link to this speech by Mr Adam Price' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-adam-price" title="Mr Adam Price">Adam Price</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Transport what assessment he has made of the percentage contribution of transport-related emissions to overall UK greenhouse gas emissions. [188478]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_381'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-jamieson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_381' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Jamieson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-jamieson" title="Mr David Jamieson">Mr. Jamieson</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The precise percentage contribution of transport-related emissions to overall UK greenhouse gas emissions depends on how broadly transport-related emissions are defined. In particular, it varies according</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1716ws' title='Col. 1716WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1716WS' name='column_1716ws' href='#column_1716ws' rel='bookmark'>1716WS</a>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_382'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-jamieson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_382' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Jamieson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-jamieson" title="Mr David Jamieson">Mr. Jamieson</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">In line with the European Commission's methodological guidance on the assessment of plans or projects significantly affecting Natura 2000 sites we take the view that consideration of alternatives is not confined to alternative local sites.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
